{"body": "I have a question, and I'm not sure this is the appropriate place to ask, but I'd really like to know the answer (or at least have a better understanding).\n\nWhy do we wind up with things like this being suggested (and often added) to Rails? Do people not understand Ruby, OO, good design? What is the benefit of divorcing Rails from Ruby? Do people find Ruby a difficult programming language? Is the goal here to get more non-programmers writing Rails?\n\n(I'm genuinely curious, because I feel that I have to understand the cause problem before I can help stop it.)", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/8390441", "created_at": "2012-09-08T16:26:49Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7520#issuecomment-8390441", "updated_at": "2012-09-08T16:26:49Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7520, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/srbaker", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/3c8c4b69930a102c3ca698cc4cbcbf0b?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F79fde5402cbc75ae0615c9ae4c335b46.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/received_events", "gravatar_id": "3c8c4b69930a102c3ca698cc4cbcbf0b", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "srbaker", "type": "User", "id": 4538, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/srbaker/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fac1bd3543c15100b6b4"}, "id": 8390441, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7520"}
